phrases: But yeah... to the kobolds, we are invaders.
It will be nice and quick.
What is that supposed to mean?
This is Yume's new skill, Star Strike.
Because limitless fear for those who do not obey!
This causes fear, making the opponent unable to make clear decisions.
This is magic only a Dark Knight can cast.
This is not what it is supposed to do!
It does seem like it is confused.
I just want to call it that!
Repeating a yesterday filled with scrapes,
We clear the path to a hopeful tomorrow.
The voice I raised upwards scattered into the air.
The reality I have gamed is hazy,
and even if I cannot see ahead of me,
I can keep moving forward on this long road
Connecting a bond covered in dust,
We join back to back in the past and future.
Repeating an answer full of mistakes,
I will reach out my hands to seek the light, again and again.
But this does not look like it is worth much.
The ones in the first level of the mine are ruffians among kobolds.
They are poorly dressed and weak.
That is why Volunteer Soldiers call them low-class kobolds or lesser kobolds.
So the others will have better talismans?
There is probably a nicer way of retrieving spoils from a fight.
To the kobolds, we are invaders.
Nothing changes even if we have pangs of guilt.
No matter if we take their nose rings off carefully or tear them off violently, the end result is still the same.
The whole thing is still the same.
Ranta does it without hesitation, but I am trying to make up for that guilt.
That might be hypocritical of me...
No matter if they are an enemy or prey, I should at least be paying my respects in this way.
The Cyrene Mine has more than ten levels.
Lesser kobolds, normal kobolds, and elder kobolds live here.
Only the elder kobolds can freely use the gondola.
There is a gondola installed in the mineshaft from the third layer down.
We will be mostly going up and down through the wells, though.
Is it because the gondola is heavily guarded?
The elders are the leaders, the normal kobolds are workers, and lesser kobolds do not hold any status.
Normal kobolds dwell in the second level down, so that is where things will get serious.
So the hard part is still to come, huh.
They are always noisy at these times.
Sleeping kobolds only wake up when there is something big going on.
It would be some easy loot.
Are you a demon or something?
I serve the Dark God Skullhell-sama.
We believe that in death, all are equal.
are the antithesis of what you call in your pretty little words common sense and morals.
It is an important concept, so I will say it a third time.
Eventually, you will fall into death's embrace anyway, so it is stupid to be bound by useless ideals.
We should be driven by things like our desires, instincts, and impulses.
That is how it should be.
And at the end, we all die, just the same.
I am listening, I am listening.
That is Shihoru's new skill, Shadow Bond.
The enemy cannot move, as if their legs are stuck to the ground.
Just like Sleepy Shadow, it becomes less effective the more worked up the opponent is.
Strong opponents can forcefully break free from the spell, though.
I just need to follow it.
When I see the streak, I need to breathe calmly.
If I change my breathing patterns, it will disappear.
There is no time to think that I cannot miss this chance.
When I see the streak, my body is already moving.
That is how it should feel.
If not, it will not succeed.
Your new spell is amazing, Shihoru.
These normal kobolds were nothing, too.
It will not be this easy from the third layer down because of the elders.
They are armed and fight using tactics.
Let us return to Ortana for now.
It is not like we cannot get back.
I am afraid of getting used to this place and becoming complacent.
If we are talking about compatibility, Ranta and I are not very much so.
We were this close to starting a fight today.
He does not seem to be getting along with Yume, Shihoru, or Merry either.
Can I just leave him as he is?
I guess I am the leader, though.
It is not like Manato really liked Ranta that much, either.
Maybe Manato did not judge him by whether he liked Ranta or not.
It did not seem like Ranta was as defiant with Manato.
He was pretty shaken up when Manato died, too.
What is the difference between Manato and me?
I initiated this... but I do not know what to say.
I feel there are things we need to talk about, though.
Well... how do you feel about things?
What is that nothing more, nothing less mean?
I feel I have been properly fulfilling my duties to the party.
Like today, I proved I could take on an opponent single-handedly.
That would have been over in an instant if we had all surrounded it.
Can you guarantee that we will always be able to do that?
If I can reliably take one on by myself, we can what... broaden our tactics.
No, I am getting too worked up.
So he is been thinking about things in his own way.
I do think that Ranta functions as our secondary tank.
This is something that Yume and I cannot do.
And of course we cannot make Merry do it.
He is been thinking about his role in this party in his own way.
I would not have known that unless you told me now.
It would have been too late after the fact if something were to happen.
So I have to consult with you for every single thing?
That is not what I mean, but I am saying that there are things I will not know unless you say them.
On top of everything, you are... easily misunderstood, you know?
It is not like you think it is a misunderstanding.
What you are really saying is that it is my fault.
We are working as a team...
And I am not working as a team?
You do not think so either?
Everybody has their strengths and weaknesses.
I almost do not think I have any strengths.
Why do I have to tell you?
So you will not say a word when it is about yourself?
Have I complained about your weaknesses?
It is because you happened to bring this stuff up that I am saying this.
If not, then I would have never brought it up myself.
I am not interested in being all chummy with you guys.
You guys can go play pretend friends without me.
If you guys hate me, go ahead and hate me.
We are a party, so I will fulfill my duty to the party.
That is what working as a team is about, right?
I am not as good as you though.
You will catch a cold sleeping out here.
I just kind of fell asleep.
I did not know what kind of knife was good, you know.
And when I asked Master, he took me to the market, you see.
And Master picked two for me.
And he said he would only buy one, so he bought one for me.
I bought the other one myself, too!
O light, return to Lumiaris' divine protection.
This is Merry's new Light Magic.
It is short range and does not do a lot of damage, but it numbs and slows down the opponent.
She wanted to increase the ways she could support Moguzo and Ranta in the front.
You will run out of breath if you keep shouting!
If you died, I would just get an extra Vice.
Right, if I remember that this is just how he is, I will not get angry.
Will I be able to let it go?
It is a one-handed attack with a longer range.
He also learned Back Thrust, an attack he can perform while backing away.
Let us all go for the elder!
We might be able to defeat him unscathed!
It is pretty different from the third level and above.
Those animals are pretty cute, huh!
I was just trying it out.
I would not really do anything.
How does just trying it out and would not really do anything make sense together?
It makes total sense to me, get it?
Then tell me what it means.
That it makes sense to you?
That is exactly what I said.
Would not it be faster for us to just kill'them?
That is not a good idea.
From the fourth level down, we will because a big commotion if we cannot kill them instantly.
Now that they have been alerted, it is better if we go down to the fifth level.
They have the advantage in open fields like this.
It has white and black patches.
the dry air after a rain,
The warmth you gave this hand
led me to a future I can treasure
I wonder when you became so strong.
I will probably find what I searched the vast world for
at the end of this journey.
I am Not Fit to Be a Leader
Now serialized on the official anime web site.
